  The real reason why they don't allow accounts to be sold is because they lose out on a lot of potential profit.  <br>
<br>
  Player A, we'll call him Bob, Bob has a 60th level and he is tired of everquest and is short on rent money.  Bingo, he decides he will sell his account.<br>
<br>
  Player B, we'll call him John, John has a friend on bobs server who is 52 and John doesn't want to level up his character all the way up. John goes to an auction site and finds bob's character for a fair price and buys it.<br>
<br>
  Sony has now gained $10.00 a month assuming bob will never play again. However, that 10.00 they gain goes to running everquest and they probably only make a fraction of that in net profit. <br>
<br>
  Now, lets say you couldn't buy accounts. John now has to buy everquest, kunark, velious, and luclin. Verrant now makes $80.00ish, most of which is net profit, and that at least is why I think they frown on the selling of accounts. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uunem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>unem</A> at: 1/30/02 10:08:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usarkaukar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarkaukar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 6:02:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22025.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dcms-kurita.net/images/images3025/1stsothdrdh.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The reason is to protect themselves from liability</span><hr size=1> Agrees with Unem.<br>
