During that time, I got to know a lot of the background philosophies of the company and as I said, all the reasons mentioned above are part of the reason.<br>
<br>
Mostly it was against &quot;the vision&quot; but the other BIG reason, at least early on was the Customer Service issue. You cannot believe the amount of calls we got from bad deals even when they knew we didn't support the sale. I shudder to think of the man-power drain that would occur if it was condoned.<br>
<br>
There is also a lot of truth to the liability thing. If you ever work for a large corp, you soon see the levels they will go to minimize liability exposure.<br>
<br>
The lack of sales revenue was never really an issue. As mentioned, Verant makes little off the real sale (heck they're giving the base game away now with magazines and Gateway computers).<br>
<br>
